-- J-Power, Kansai Electric to Sign Indonesia Grid-Design Contract With JICA
-- Shigeru Sato
-- 2010-06-16T01:58:58Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-16/j-power-kansai-electric-to-sign-indonesia-grid-design-contract-with-jica.html

          
          
             Electric Power Development Co. and
Kansai Electric Power Co. will sign a 3.8 billion yen contract
this month with state aid agency Japan International Cooperation
Agency to design a national power grid for Indonesia, Emi
Aizawa, a JICA spokeswoman, said today by telephone from Tokyo.  
 The two companies will design a 200 billion-yen, 600-
kilometer power-transmission-line project connecting the islands
of Sumatra and Java, she said.    
